1- Create OpenShift Online Account
 
2-Configure Openshift client tools

 $ sudo apt-get install ruby-full
 $ ruby -e 'puts "Welcome to Ruby"'
 $ sudo apt-get install rubygems
 $ sudo apt-get install git-core
 $ sudo gem install rhc
 $ export PATH=/var/lib/gems/2.1.0/bin:$PATH
 $ echo $PATH
 $ sudo ln -s /var/lib/gems/2.1.0/bin/rhc* /usr/bin/
 $ rhc setup
   -->step by step (account, PKI key, token, etc)
   -->check account settings
3-Create application (using web console or commande line tools)
-Add PHP5, MySQL, phpmyadmin.
-Access to application URL
4-clone application from Openshift
$ git clone ssh://582e26660c1e6674a0000016@gestionetudiants-samplewalid.rhcloud.com/~/git/gestionetudiants.git/ MyApp
5-Update (Add new files)

6-Push application into OpenShift

$ git add .
$ git commit -m"adding files"
$ git push

7-Access to URL application to see new update



